## Feature Flag Rollback

### Instant Disable Pattern

```python
# Application checks feature flag at runtime
if feature_flags.is_enabled("new_checkout_flow"):
    return new_checkout(request)
else:
    return legacy_checkout(request)
```

### Rollback via Feature Flag

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 | Disable feature flag (no deploy) |
| 2 | Traffic routes to legacy path |
| 3 | Investigate and fix |
| 4 | Re-enable when ready |
| 5 | Remove flag and legacy code in future release |

### Feature Flag Rollback Checklist

- [ ] Feature flags support instant disable
- [ ] Disable does not require deployment
- [ ] Legacy path remains functional
- [ ] Flag state is logged for audit
- [ ] Runbook documents flag disable procedure

---

## Rollback Decision Matrix

| Scenario | Automated | Manual | Data Migration |
|----------|-----------|--------|----------------|
| App deploy, error spike | Yes | Fallback | N/A |
| Config change, latency | Yes | Fallback | N/A |
| Schema migration | No | Yes | Yes |
| Feature flag cutover | No | Yes | Maybe |
| Infrastructure change | Depends | Yes | N/A |

---

## Post-Rollback

- [ ] Verify metrics normalized
- [ ] Document root cause
- [ ] Create incident report
- [ ] Update runbook if procedure changed
- [ ] Schedule post-mortem if significant impact
- [ ] Add monitoring or automation to prevent recurrence
